{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "FireHeatFlux",
        "description": "Sensible and latent heat flux density released by burning fuel, per Eqs. 4–5 of Mandel et al. (2011). Migrated from WildlandFire.jl@126976f2 src/level_set_fire_spread.jl:295 (`FireHeatFlux` @component). Observed-only: fuel_burn_rate, w_l, h_fuel, M_f are inputs (parameters); phi_h and phi_q are algebraic outputs.",
        "tags": [
            "wildland_fire",
            "level_set",
            "fire_heat_flux",
            "observed-only",
            "mandel2011"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-06T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "WildlandFire.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (mdl-gwf7)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Mandel, J., Beezley, J.D., and Kochanski, A.K. (2011). Coupled atmosphere-wildland fire modeling with WRF 3.3 and SFIRE 2011. Geosci. Model Dev., 4, 591–610. doi:10.5194/gmd-4-591-2011 — Equations 4 (sensible heat flux) and 5 (latent heat flux)."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "FireHeatFlux": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: WildlandFire.jl@126976f2508ceacca6c486b21ae6da5b168c6f46:src/level_set_fire_spread.jl:295\nUpstream `FireHeatFlux` is an MTK `@component` whose three driving inputs (w_l, h_fuel, M_f) are `@parameters`, whose `fuel_burn_rate(t)` is a `@variables` driven externally (in the parent system, the FuelConsumption component supplies it as is_burning*F/T_f, the magnitude of -dF/dt), and whose two outputs (phi_h, phi_q) are time-indexed `@variables` defined by the two algebraic equations. The standalone .esm here folds `fuel_burn_rate` into the parameter set so the component is well-posed without a parent — matching the pattern used elsewhere in the rig (see components/aerosol/aq_eq/water.esm and components/wildland_fire/rothermel/live_fuel_moisture_extinction.esm) where externally-driven `@variables` and `@constants` are unified into ESM `parameter` declarations. The three upstream `@constants` (one=1.0, water_combustion_ratio=0.56, L_water=2.5e6) are likewise preserved as parameters with the upstream defaults.\n\nThe equations are the Mandel et al. (2011) closed-form sensible/latent heat flux densities:\n  phi_h = fuel_burn_rate * w_l * h_fuel / (one + M_f)             (Eq. 4)\n  phi_q = fuel_burn_rate * (M_f + water_combustion_ratio) / (one + M_f) * L_water * w_l   (Eq. 5)\n— preserved verbatim (the ordering of the multiplications inside phi_q matches the upstream Julia source so float64 roundoff is bit-identical).\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-12): observed-only algebraic system (no ODE integration); both equations are short chains of multiply/divide on hardware-supported intrinsics, so float64 roundoff is at the ULP level (~1e-15). 1e-12 is comfortably above that and below any plausible physical-discrimination scale on heat-flux quantities (fluxes range ~1e2 to ~1e5 W/m² across realistic Anderson fuel models)."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1.0e-12
            },
            "variables": {
                "fuel_burn_rate": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1/s",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Rate of fuel consumption (-dF/dt); driven externally by FuelConsumption in the coupled system"
                },
                "w_l": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/m^2",
                    "default": 0.166,
                    "description": "Total fuel load (Anderson fuel model 1 default)"
                },
                "h_fuel": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "J/kg",
                    "default": 1.8608e7,
                    "description": "Heat content of dry fuel (Anderson 1982 / WRF-SFIRE Table 1: 8000 BTU/lb = 1.8608e7 J/kg)"
                },
                "M_f": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.08,
                    "description": "Fuel moisture content (dimensionless mass fraction)"
                },
                "one": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Unity dimensionless constant (preserved from upstream MTK @constants for unit-balancing)"
                },
                "water_combustion_ratio": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.56,
                    "description": "Estimated mass ratio of water output from combustion to dry fuel (Mandel et al. 2011)"
                },
                "L_water": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "J/kg",
                    "default": 2.5e6,
                    "description": "Latent heat of condensation of water at 0°C (Mandel et al. 2011)"
                },
                "phi_h": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "description": "Sensible heat flux density"
                },
                "phi_q": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "description": "Latent heat (moisture) flux density"
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": "phi_h",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": ["fuel_burn_rate", "w_l", "h_fuel"]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": ["one", "M_f"]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "phi_q",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            "fuel_burn_rate",
                            {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "+",
                                        "args": ["M_f", "water_combustion_ratio"]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "+",
                                        "args": ["one", "M_f"]
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            "L_water",
                            "w_l"
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "zero_burn_rate",
                    "description": "No fuel burning (fuel_burn_rate = 0). Both fluxes vanish independent of w_l, h_fuel, M_f. Sanity check that the algebraic prefactor is correctly multiplicative.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "fuel_burn_rate": 0.0,
                        "w_l": 0.5,
                        "h_fuel": 1.86e7,
                        "M_f": 0.08
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "phi_h", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "phi_q", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "dry_fuel_M_f_zero",
                    "description": "Dry fuel (M_f = 0). Eq. 4 simplifies to phi_h = fuel_burn_rate * w_l * h_fuel; Eq. 5 to phi_q = fuel_burn_rate * water_combustion_ratio * L_water * w_l. fbr=1e-3, w_l=1, h=1.86e7 → phi_h = 18600, phi_q = 0.56 * 2.5e6 * 1e-3 = 1400.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "fuel_burn_rate": 1.0e-3,
                        "w_l": 1.0,
                        "h_fuel": 1.86e7,
                        "M_f": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "phi_h", "time": 0.0, "expected": 18600.0 },
                        { "variable": "phi_q", "time": 0.0, "expected": 1400.0000000000002 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "moist_fuel_clean_arithmetic",
                    "description": "Moderate moisture (M_f = 0.1) with fbr=2e-3, w_l=2, h=1.86e7. phi_h = 2e-3·2·1.86e7 / 1.1 = 74400 / 1.1 = 67636.36…; phi_q = 2e-3·0.66/1.1·2.5e6·2 = 6600/1.1 = 6000 (exact rational).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "fuel_burn_rate": 2.0e-3,
                        "w_l": 2.0,
                        "h_fuel": 1.86e7,
                        "M_f": 0.1
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "phi_h", "time": 0.0, "expected": 67636.36363636363 },
                        { "variable": "phi_q", "time": 0.0, "expected": 5999.999999999999 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "saturated_moisture_M_f_one",
                    "description": "Saturated fuel (M_f = 1.0). The (one + M_f) denominator becomes 2; phi_h is halved relative to the dry case. fbr=1e-3, w_l=1, h=2e7 → phi_h = 1e-3·1·2e7/2 = 10000; phi_q = 1e-3·1.56/2·2.5e6·1 = 1950.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "fuel_burn_rate": 1.0e-3,
                        "w_l": 1.0,
                        "h_fuel": 2.0e7,
                        "M_f": 1.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "phi_h", "time": 0.0, "expected": 10000.0 },
                        { "variable": "phi_q", "time": 0.0, "expected": 1950.0000000000002 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "low_load_high_burn",
                    "description": "Low fuel load (w_l=0.5) with fast burn rate (fbr=5e-3), light moisture (M_f=0.05), reduced heat content (h=1.0e7). phi_h = 5e-3·0.5·1.0e7/1.05 = 25000/1.05 = 23809.52…; phi_q = 5e-3·0.61/1.05·2.5e6·0.5 = 3812.5/1.05 = 3630.95….",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "fuel_burn_rate": 5.0e-3,
                        "w_l": 0.5,
                        "h_fuel": 1.0e7,
                        "M_f": 0.05
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "phi_h", "time": 0.0, "expected": 23809.52380952381 },
                        { "variable": "phi_q", "time": 0.0, "expected": 3630.9523809523816 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "anderson_fuel_1_grass",
                    "description": "Representative grass-fuel scenario per Anderson (1982) fuel model 1 / Mandel et al. (2011) Table 1: w_l=0.166 kg/m², h=1.8608e7 J/kg (8000 BTU/lb), M_f=0.08 (8% moisture), fbr=1/119 s⁻¹ (T_f=119 s, F=1, is_burning=1). phi_h = (1/119)·0.166·1.8608e7/1.08 ≈ 24034.6 W/m²; phi_q ≈ 2066.6 W/m² — order of magnitude matches Mandel et al. (2011) §3.2.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "fuel_burn_rate": 0.008403361344537815,
                        "w_l": 0.166,
                        "h_fuel": 1.8608e7,
                        "M_f": 0.08
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "phi_h", "time": 0.0, "expected": 24034.60939931528 },
                        { "variable": "phi_q", "time": 0.0, "expected": 2066.604419545596 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "ratio_phi_q_over_phi_h",
                    "description": "Cross-check the Mandel et al. (2011) ratio identity: phi_q / phi_h = (M_f + water_combustion_ratio) * L_water / h_fuel — independent of fuel_burn_rate and w_l. Pick fbr=4e-3, w_l=1.5, h=1.5e7, M_f=0.2. phi_h = 4e-3·1.5·1.5e7/1.2 = 90000/1.2 = 75000 exact; phi_q = 4e-3·0.76/1.2·2.5e6·1.5 = 11400/1.2 = 9500 exact; ratio = 9500/75000 = 0.7600/6.0 = 0.12666… = 0.76·2.5e6/1.5e7 ✓.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "fuel_burn_rate": 4.0e-3,
                        "w_l": 1.5,
                        "h_fuel": 1.5e7,
                        "M_f": 0.2
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "phi_h", "time": 0.0, "expected": 75000.0 },
                        { "variable": "phi_q", "time": 0.0, "expected": 9500.000000000002 }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "phi_h_vs_M_f_sweep",
                    "description": "Sweep M_f over the realistic atmospheric range (0 to 0.5) at fixed fuel_burn_rate, w_l, h_fuel. Surfaces the (1 + M_f)⁻¹ damping of the sensible heat flux as fuel moisture rises — the dominant qualitative feature of Mandel et al. (2011) Eq. 4.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "fuel_burn_rate": 1.0e-2,
                        "w_l": 0.166,
                        "h_fuel": 1.8608e7
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "M_f",
                                "range": { "start": 0.0, "stop": 0.5, "count": 26, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "phi_h_curve",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Sensible heat flux as a function of fuel moisture content.",
                            "x": { "variable": "M_f",   "label": "M_f (mass fraction)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "phi_h", "label": "phi_h (W/m²)" }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "phi_q_curve",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Latent heat flux as a function of fuel moisture content — increases with M_f because the (M_f + 0.56) numerator dominates over the (1 + M_f) denominator at low M_f.",
                            "x": { "variable": "M_f",   "label": "M_f (mass fraction)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "phi_q", "label": "phi_q (W/m²)" }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "phi_h_heatmap_burn_rate_w_l",
                    "description": "Two-dimensional sweep over (fuel_burn_rate, w_l) at fixed h_fuel and M_f. Both fluxes are bilinear in (fbr, w_l), so the surface should be a smooth product map — useful for visual sanity-checking the equation structure.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "h_fuel": 1.8608e7,
                        "M_f": 0.08
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "fuel_burn_rate",
                                "range": { "start": 0.0, "stop": 0.02, "count": 21, "scale": "linear" }
                            },
                            {
                                "parameter": "w_l",
                                "range": { "start": 0.1, "stop": 3.0, "count": 21, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "phi_h_surface",
                            "type": "heatmap",
                            "description": "Sensible heat flux as a function of fuel burn rate and fuel load.",
                            "x": { "variable": "fuel_burn_rate", "label": "fuel_burn_rate (1/s)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "w_l",            "label": "w_l (kg/m²)" },
                            "value": { "variable": "phi_h", "reduce": "final" }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}
